description: Lists the network interfaces specified in a decoder manifest.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the decoder manifest to list information about.

parameters.name: nextToken
parameters.description: A pagination token for the next set of results. If the results of a search are large, only a portion of the results are returned, and a nextToken pagination token is returned in the response. To retrieve the next set of results, reissue the search request and include the returned token. When all results have been returned, the response does not contain a pagination token value.

nested_items.name: networkInterfaces
nested_items.description: A list of information about network interfaces.

nested_items.name: interfaceId
nested_items.description: The ID of the network interface.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The network protocol for the vehicle. For example, CAN_SIGNAL specifies a protocol that defines how data is communicated between electronic control units (ECUs). OBD_SIGNAL specifies a protocol that defines how self-diagnostic data is communicated between ECUs.

nested_items.name: canInterface
nested_items.description: Information about a network interface specified by the Controller Area Network (CAN) protocol.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The unique name of the interface.

nested_items.name: protocolName
nested_items.description: The name of the communication protocol for the interface.

nested_items.name: protocolVersion
nested_items.description: The version of the communication protocol for the interface.

nested_items.name: obdInterface
nested_items.description: Information about a network interface specified by the on-board diagnostic (OBD) II protocol.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the interface.

nested_items.name: requestMessageId
nested_items.description: The ID of the message requesting vehicle data.

nested_items.name: obdStandard
nested_items.description: The standard OBD II PID.

nested_items.name: pidRequestIntervalSeconds
nested_items.description: The maximum number message requests per second.

nested_items.name: dtcRequestIntervalSeconds
nested_items.description: The maximum number message requests per diagnostic trouble code per second.

nested_items.name: useExtendedIds
nested_items.description: Whether to use extended IDs in the message.

nested_items.name: hasTransmissionEcu
nested_items.description: Whether the vehicle has a transmission control module (TCM).

nested_items.name: vehicleMiddleware
nested_items.description: The vehicle middleware defined as a type of network interface. Examples of vehicle middleware include ROS2 and SOME/IP.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the vehicle middleware.

nested_items.name: protocolName
nested_items.description: The protocol name of the vehicle middleware.

nested_items.name: customDecodingInterface
nested_items.description: Information about a custom network interface.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the interface.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The token to retrieve the next set of results, or null if there are no more results.
